  "prompt": "How do I know true love?",
  "response": "Knowing true love can be a complex and deeply personal experience, but here are some signs that might help you identify it:\n\n1. **Unconditional Acceptance**: True love involves accepting each other as you are, flaws and all. You feel comfortable being your authentic self around your partner.\n\n2. **Mutual Respect**: There's a deep sense of respect for each other\u2019s feelings, opinions, and boundaries. You value each other's individuality and support personal growth.\n\n3. **Trust**: You have confidence in your partner and feel secure in the relationship. Trust forms the foundation of true love.\n\n4. **Effective Communication**: You can openly discuss your thoughts and feelings, and you both actively listen to each other. Conflicts are resolved through healthy communication.\n\n5. **Empathy and Compassion**: You genuinely care about your partner's well-being and happiness, and you\u2019re willing to support them through both good times and bad.\n\n6. **Shared Values and Goals**: While you may not agree on everything, you share core values and long-term goals, which help you grow together as a couple.\n\n7. **Joy and Laughter**: True love often brings joy and laughter. You enjoy each other's company and have fun together.\n\n8. **Commitment**: There's a strong sense of dedication to the relationship. Both partners are willing to work through challenges and grow together over time.\n\n9. **Sacrifice and Compromise**: You're willing to make sacrifices and compromises for the sake of the relationship, but this is balanced and not one-sided.\n\n10. **Physical and Emotional Intimacy**: There's a strong connection both physically and emotionally. Intimacy goes beyond physical attraction and includes emotional closeness.\n\n11. **Feeling at Peace**: Being with your partner feels right and brings a sense of calm and peace. You feel at home with them.\n\nRemember, true love is not perfect, and every relationship has its ups and downs. It's about finding someone with whom you can navigate life's journey together, supporting each other along the way.",
